programme.title: The Murder of Mary Magdalene: Genocide of the Holy Bloodline
programme.desc: Was Mary Magdalene murdered? Did the Catholic Church conspire to eradicate the Holy Bloodline from existence? To some Mary Magdalene was the wife or consort of Jesus Christ. The arena along with the idea of a Holy Bloodline descended from Jesus and Mary. In this unique film we journey to places never before researched in connection with this story. We venture into the heart of ancient Lincoln, England, and uncover a tale so mysterious, so at odds with the accepted norm, that we are forced to question everything we previously held to be true. We track down unknown texts, journey on a treasure hunt across Lincoln county and discover the final resting place of Mary Magdalene herself. See the locations filmed for The Da Vinci Code movie and find an English Jerusalem. Come with us as we go beneath the streets into ancient tunnels to find the tomb explore little known Templar sites. Watch as Dan Green goes clue by clue to unravel a magnificent trail of codes and ciphers.Join us on an amazing journey into a world full of synchronicity.

programme.title: Paranormal Horrors of The True North
programme.desc: Canada has a rich and colorful history which has resulted in a variety of paranormal phenomena from coast to coast. Outdoor enthusiasts hiking the Bruce Trail in Ancaster, Ontario often find themselves at the remains of a once great mansion. Known as the Hermitage Ruins, visitors encounter two very different spirits on a regular basis. The first is a coachman who hung himself on the property and still carries the severed noose around his neck. The second apparition is a woman who once owned the mansion and loved it so much that she refused to leave even after it burned down. The “Espirit” is Montreal’s hottest nightclub. While it has had many names over the years, one thing has remained constant – it’s ghostly apparitions. During the latest renovations, many workers witnessed a large ball of light floating towards them, and even passing through them. Others saw the ghost of a woman, with a horrific scar running the length of her pale torso. The War of 1812 was a definitive moment in Canadian history, inflicting thousands of casualties. One fight in particular left an impression on Niagara Falls, Ontario. The Battle for Lundy’s Lane was so grueling; it claimed hundreds of lives in mere hours. At Drummond Hill Cemetery three such ghostly casualties remain; forever on duty watching the gates. Prepare for an exciting thrill ride to some of Canada's most haunted locations.

programme.title: Lady of the Dark: Genesis of the Serpent Vampire
programme.desc: The old legends tell of serpents giving the seed of knowledge to mankind. As time passed, religions emerged around the world that revered and worshiped it above all else. This knowledge was so great and powerful that it was eventually forced underground and replaced with the cross by ruling factions who sought to destroy all those deemed serpent worshippers. But there was a secret prophecy hidden and protected by an elite few. An old parchment, battered and worn over time, was kept safe through the ages. It claimed that one day the genesis of the serpent would begin again, because the seed of the serpent cannot die and will be re-born. Eve, an unsuspecting married woman, is selected for the re-birth and transformed into The Lady of the Dark - emerging as a ravenous, instinctual killer who shows no mercy.

programme.title: Western Hunting & Conservation Expo / Our Wyld Life / EP1

Welcome to Our Wyld Life where host Kristy Titus and her husband, Yogi, take viewers along on their day-to-day lives, full of adventure. After relocating to Wyoming, hunting, outdoor and shooting sports recreation are literally in their backyard. The couple is truly making their home on the range while developing their new homestead and enjoying life in the cowboy state.
In our premiere episode, we show you a little bit of what it's like being a Wyoming resident, in the winter. After a tough start, Kristy makes it a great week with familiar faces and many new ones, in what is one of the most fun shows of the year! If you didn't make it in 2023, it's a must to attend next year! Also, you'll be introduced to the newest (and longest eared) members of the family! Kristy shows off her baby mules...lots more of the mules to come! When they aren't out on an adventure trekking deep into the backcountry with their horses and mules, you'll find them preparing for the next opportunity to do so.
Our Wyld Life presents the journey of life out west in Wyoming.

programme.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
programme.desc: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, 100-dollar counterfeit bills and drugs, all entering US ports undetected. Calverese comes up with a brilliant take-down scheme to nab everyone involved in the smuggling - a personal invitation to his fabricated wedding. After receiving Rolex watches and other gifts, Calverese and the FBI do a takedown of the wedding guests.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: The Last Dance
programme.desc: In Silverthorne, Colorado, a photographer's wife seems to have mysteriously vanished in the night, until detectives learn he has a violent past. In Darby, Montana, a husband is dead, and Police have two suspects - his wife and mistress.

programme.title: Turmoil
programme.desc: In Easton, Pennsylvania, a lesbian love triangle spins out of control while in Gillette, Wyoming, a desperate housewife has a shocking tale of murder and revenge.

programme.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
programme.desc: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, 100-dollar counterfeit bills and drugs, all entering US ports undetected. Calverese comes up with a brilliant take-down scheme to nab everyone involved in the smuggling - a personal invitation to his fabricated wedding. After receiving Rolex watches and other gifts, Calverese and the FBI do a takedown of the wedding guests.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: The Last Dance
programme.desc: In Silverthorne, Colorado, a photographer's wife seems to have mysteriously vanished in the night, until detectives learn he has a violent past. In Darby, Montana, a husband is dead, and Police have two suspects - his wife and mistress.

programme.title: Turmoil
programme.desc: In Easton, Pennsylvania, a lesbian love triangle spins out of control while in Gillette, Wyoming, a desperate housewife has a shocking tale of murder and revenge.

programme.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
programme.desc: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, 100-dollar counterfeit bills and drugs, all entering US ports undetected. Calverese comes up with a brilliant take-down scheme to nab everyone involved in the smuggling - a personal invitation to his fabricated wedding. After receiving Rolex watches and other gifts, Calverese and the FBI do a takedown of the wedding guests.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
programme.desc: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, 100-dollar counterfeit bills and drugs, all entering US ports undetected. Calverese comes up with a brilliant take-down scheme to nab everyone involved in the smuggling - a personal invitation to his fabricated wedding. After receiving Rolex watches and other gifts, Calverese and the FBI do a takedown of the wedding guests.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: Operation Chokehold: Busting Boston's Mob
programme.desc: FBI agent Vince delaMontaigne infiltrates the powerful La Cosa Nostra mob in an attempt to break their stranglehold on organized crime in Boston. To do this, delaMontaigne befriends Biagio DiGiacomo in the restaurant he owns and becomes one of the regulars who make deals and plot various ways to make a dishonest dollar. His efforts finally pay off but not before he's entangled in illegal betting, drug sales and extortion simply by playing his undercover role so well and being in the right place at the right time.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.

programme.title: The Last Dance
programme.desc: In Silverthorne, Colorado, a photographer's wife seems to have mysteriously vanished in the night, until detectives learn he has a violent past. In Darby, Montana, a husband is dead, and Police have two suspects - his wife and mistress.

programme.title: Turmoil
programme.desc: In Easton, Pennsylvania, a lesbian love triangle spins out of control while in Gillette, Wyoming, a desperate housewife has a shocking tale of murder and revenge.

programme.title: Operation Royal Charm: Smuggler's Blues
programme.desc: FBI agent Lou Calverese goes undercover to infiltrate the lucrative world of international smuggling. What begins as a case of black market cigarettes soon involves military weapons, 100-dollar counterfeit bills and drugs, all entering US ports undetected. Calverese comes up with a brilliant take-down scheme to nab everyone involved in the smuggling - a personal invitation to his fabricated wedding. After receiving Rolex watches and other gifts, Calverese and the FBI do a takedown of the wedding guests.

programme.title: Operation Nautilus: Pakistani Hash On The High Seas
programme.desc: US Customs agent Paul DeCotiis is part of an international undercover plan to intercept 70 tons of Pakistani hashish in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. Customs uses a seized boat to meet the traffickers near Midway Island. High seas prevent most of the hash being transferred to the undercover boat, but Customs follows the drugs to the traffickers. DeCotiis is the point man throughout the operation between the Customs undercover team and a group of Canadian hippies hoping for a big payday. DeCotiis finally delivers the hash to the traffickers, resulting in several life sentences.

programme.title: Operation Shattered Shield: Nabbing Dirty Cops
programme.desc: FBI agent Juan Jackson goes undercover to build a case against corrupt New Orleans police officers, in the most corrupt city in America. Jackson learns that cops are ripping off street dealers, stealing their drugs and profiting from the sale of narcotics. They're using intimidation, violence, and ultimately, murder to silence witnesses who might consider testifying against them. Jackson befriends the corrupt cops to record their conversations and he becomes a target when they order a hit on him. In the end, 23 officers are indicted on various charges and the case forever changes the New Orleans police department.
